title: Bigfoot believers swap stories at annual upstate New York retreat [Photos]
text:
Bigfoot believers swap stories at annual upstate New York retreat 
THE ASSOCIATED PRESS Saturday, October 24, 2015 02:45 PM EDT Bigfoot retreat in New York state Previous Next 
Plaster casts and framed photos line one of the display tables at the 4th annual Chautauqua Lake Bigfoot Expo in Chautauqua, N.Y., Saturday, Oct. 24, 2015. Believers and the curious gather in the rural western New York county to swap stories and hear lectures about the legendary Sasquatch. (AP Photo/Carolyn Thompson) AP 
Peter Wiemer delivers opening remarks at the 4th annual Chautauqua Lake Bigfoot Expo in Chautauqua, N.Y., Saturday, Oct. 24, 2015. Wiemer created the annual conference to increase tourism in the rural western New York county but has since met dozens of people who claim they have seen the legendary Sasquatch in Chautauqua and adjoining counties. (AP Photo/Carolyn Thompson) AP 
Conservationist Tricia Bergstue from the Chautauqua Watershed Conservancy and field biologist Jamie Haight display stuffed Bigfoot toys at the Chautauqua Lake Bigfoot Expo in Chautauqua, N.Y., Saturday, Oct. 24, 2015. The Chautauqua Watershed Conservancy offered expo attendees the chance to "adopt" a Sasquatch for a $25 donation to help protect the habitat of all creatures. (AP Photo/Carolyn Thompson) AP
